name babel
category Package
revision 78888
shortdesc Multilingual support for LaTeX, LuaLaTeX, XeLaTeX, and Plain TeX
longdesc Babel is the multilingual environment for LaTeX (tailored for
longdesc LuaTeX, pdfTeX and XeTeX), and sometimes Plain. Its aim is to
longdesc provide a comprehensive localization framework for different
longdesc languages, scripts and cultures based on the latest advances on
longdesc international standards (Unicode, W3C, OpenType). It supports
longdesc about 300 languages (with various levels of coverage) across
longdesc about 45 scripts, including complex (like CJK, Indic) and RTL
longdesc ones. Besides the traditional .ldf files, there are many
longdesc locales built on a modern core that utilizes descriptive .ini
longdesc files, with tools providing precise control over hyphenation
longdesc and line breaking, captions, date formats (across various
longdesc calendars), spacing, transliteration, numbering and other
longdesc locale-specific typographical rules.
